    title2: "0220. According to the “point system”:",
    link3: "",
    guid: "",
    description4: "<div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left\"><ul><li><span>Only the traffic court is entitled to revoke a driver’s license.</span></li><li><span>Only a police officer is entitled to revoke a driver’s license and to require a driver to undergo examinations.</span></li><li><span>The Licensing Authority is not authorized to revoke a driver’s license.</span></li><li><span id=\"correctAnswer0220\">The Licensing Authority is entitled to require a driver that incurred demerit points to undergo examinations, and it is also entitled to revoke his license.</span></li></ul><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: right;padding-top: 4px;\"><span>| «C1» | «C» | «D» | «A» | «1» | «В» | </span><span style=\"float: left;\"><button type=\"button\" onclick=\"var correctAnswer=document.getElementById('correctAnswer0220');correctAnswer.style.background='yellow'\">Correct Answer</button></span></div></div>",
