    title2: "1639. What risk do riders of two-wheelers face while passing between two rows of cars that stand before an intersection?",
    link3: "",
    guid: "",
    description4: "<div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left\"><ul><li><span>There is no risk, as there is always enough space for two-wheelers to pass comfortably and safely.</span></li><li><span>The risk is that at the beginning of the row, next to the intersection, there is no more space left because there are many two-wheelers standing there.</span></li><li><span id=\"correctAnswer1639\">They might hit pedestrians who are not using a regulated pedestrian crossing. </span></li><li><span>They might be hit by cigarette butts thrown by vehicle drivers.</span></li></ul><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: right;padding-top: 4px;\"><span>| «A» | </span><span style=\"float: left;\"><button type=\"button\" onclick=\"var correctAnswer=document.getElementById('correctAnswer1639');correctAnswer.style.background='yellow'\">Correct Answer</button></span></div></div>",
